  <span id="freeText11612606098331973937" style="display:none">In an ever expanding global community, resulting in the elimination or reduction of boundaries separating countries, economies, cultures and people, there is little doubt we need universal, or at least globally recognized ethics. Otherwise our future is likely to be marked by increasing tensions, divisions, conflict and even war between nations. Ethics for The New Millennium is a good start in trying to identify what a global system of ethics might look like. At the very least, another secular world view by the Dalai Lama intended to encourage harmony, cooperation, compassion and of course, personal well-being.</span>
